# Kiro Directory - Git Safety Rules

# CRITICAL: Never commit secrets or credentials
*.env
*.env.*
!*.env.example
.env.local
.env.*.local

# API keys and tokens
**/api-keys.json
**/credentials.json
**/secrets.json
**/tokens.json
**/*secret*
**/*credential*
**/*password*
**/*token*
**/*key*.json

# Supabase credentials
**/supabase-credentials.json
**/supabase-keys.json

# Database connection strings
**/database-url.txt
**/connection-string.txt

# Private configuration
**/private-config.json
**/local-config.json

# User-specific data
**/user-data/
**/personal/

# Temporary files
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.log
**/*.tmp
**/*.temp

# Build artifacts (if any get generated here)
**/.next/
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/

# IDE specific files
**/.vscode/settings.json
**/.idea/

# Backup files
**/*.bak
**/*.backup
**/*.old

# Notes that might contain sensitive info
**/NOTES.txt
**/TODO-private.md
**/scratch.md

# Allow these important files
!.gitignore
!steering/*.md
!specs/**/requirements.md
!specs/**/design.md
!specs/**/tasks.md
!specs/**/*.md

# Documentation is safe to commit
!**/*.md

# Configuration templates are safe
!**/*.example
!**/*.template
